FBIS4-63225 "drsov098_a_94029" FBIS-SOV-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS PRC Concerned Over Dalai Lama Visit to Moscow PRC Concerned Over Dalai Lama Visit to Moscow LD2005082394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0739 GMT 20 May 94 LD2005082394 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Andrey Kirillov] [Text] Moscow May 20 TASS -- The Chinese Embassy in Russia expressed "concern" over the visit of the Dalai Lama to Moscow. Spokesman of the embassy Zhang Zhiming told TASS on Friday that "China views the activities of the Dalai Lama as political in their essence and aimed at splitting the country". The Chinese Embassy "attentively and with great concern follows the activities of the Dalai Lama" in the Russian capital, he added. The spokesman stressed that Russian-Chinese relations are developing in a good way and that the basic principles of such relations had been fixed in a number of agreements. "The Chinese side hopes that the Russian Government will abide by the principles regarding the Dalai Lama", he stressed. The spokesman expressed hope that the stay of the Buddhist leader in Moscow will not acquire an official character. If he holds meeting with any officials this may result in complications", he warned. On Thursday sources in the Russian Foreign Ministry said Dalai Lama is on a private visit and no official contacts with him are planned. Russia views Tibet as an integral part of China and treasures relations with that country, according to the sources.
